You just said you were using an NES-on-a-chip. It would appear to be very likely that it is NOT a perfect copy, as a real NES PAL PPU (RP2C07) provides a full 70 scanlines between NMI/VBLANK and the beginning of the next frame.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=7">Quietust</a> — Sat Nov 05, 2005 8:49 pm</p><hr />
