<entry>
<author><name><![CDATA[Disch]]></name></author>
<updated>2005-11-05T19:35:22-07:00</updated>
<published>2005-11-05T19:35:22-07:00</published>
<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=634&amp;p=6290#p6290</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=634&amp;p=6290#p6290"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[NTSC/PAL PPU]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=634&amp;p=6290#p6290"><![CDATA[
NMI driven PAL games which use CPU-cycle counting IRQ timers (such as Mr. Gimmick) will not work properly if there's only 20 scanlines between NMI and rendering -- you need the full 70.<br /><br />Other PAL games which don't rely on sprite-0 hit or IRQ counters ... using nothing but cycle-timed code (PAL version of Balloon fight, for example) will not scroll properly unless there's 70 scanlines between NMI and the start of the frame.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=33">Disch</a> — Sat Nov 05, 2005 7:35 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
</entry>
